It is headquartered in Gallatin, Tennessee. Ted and Doris Isaacson launched Servpro Industries, Inc. in 1967 as a painting business in Sacramento, California.

namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In this video, we will see how to create virtual blocks and PDF block templates.
With the virtual blocks feature, the admin can split a single PDF block into multiple blocks virtually.
Let's take a look at this business card template which is a PDF block template.
In this template, you can see that in the address to block 3, details, city, state, and zip code have been mentioned.
With the help of a virtual block, we can split this into three different blocks without affecting the alignment of the blocks.
So let's get started.
Go to the Admin panel, navigate to the Templates section and then click on the PDF Block Templates.
Select a template, click on the Actions button and then select the Manage Blocks option.
On the Manage Blocks page, you can see all the blocks added to the template.
Locate the address to block as we will be creating virtual blocks for this one.
So to create the virtual blocks you just need to add the syntax which is the curly braces and straight line before and after the city, state and zip code.
That is curly braces and straight line before and after miscateen IA and five to 761.
Just change these values to city, state and zip code and then save the changes made.
Don't forget to update the preview of the template.
This will automatically convert into three different virtual blocks.
Here you can verify the three different blocks have been created.
Now to check how this will work in the front store, let's go back to our business card template and refresh the page.
Here you can easily identify the three new blocks on the left hand side.
Also, if any customer does not define city, state or zip code and keeps the value blank, then the alignment will be managed automatically.
In the same way you can create virtual blocks for other blocks and fields in the admin panel.
That's it.
You have successfully created virtual blocks for your PDF block templates.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
